{"tid":1437092,"cid":1,"subCid":0,"title":"緊急！應Reddit:英文宣傳單張！[[Emergency: tourists safety advices]]","createTime":"2019-08-09T12:26:08.000Z","updateTime":"2019-08-10T17:33:49.000Z","uid":302212,"like":16,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":26,"replies":[{"pid":"2a497330d80965fd068cd750589f2a91df31cbaf","tid":1437092,"uid":302212,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-08-09T12:26:08.000Z","msg":"[[Emergency: tourists safety advices]]<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\nHow to stay safe:<br />\nStay tune on radios, television broadcasts and news papers for top stories. <br />\n<br />\n1.South China morning post<br />\n2.RTHK 4 &amp; 3<br />\n3.Peal TV <br />\n<br />\nMost importantly, take &lsquo;schedule for upcoming protests&rsquo; leaflets <br />\n<br />\nWhat should you do if you approached or prosecuted by police<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/touch.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />? <br />\n<br />\n3 Dos<br />\n1. Ask the police to show his warrant card <br />\n2. Show your passport<br />\n3. Contact a lawyer <br />\n<br />\n3 Don&rsquo;t <br />\n1. Unlock your phone <br />\n2. Sign any protocols <br />\n3. Say anything <br />\n<br />\nEssentials:<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/wink.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n1. Water <br />\n2. Face masks<br />\n3. Umbrella <br />\n4. Phone<br />\n<br />\n[legal advices]<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/yo.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\nCivil human right front: 65499452(Wts only) <br />\n<br />\nBull of Fire: 67336687<br />\n<br />\nUniversities upfront: <br />\nHKU: 91390589<br />\nCU: 94433449 <br />\nUST: 60196339<br />\nCITYI:95454172<br />\nPolyU: 68000560<br />\nBU:61103860 <br />\n<br />\nMr. Ng: 26081400<br />\n<br />\nDirectory to consulate (phone number): <a href=\"http://www.discoverhongkong.com/eng/plan-your-trip/traveller-info/immigration-and-customs/foreign-consulates.jsp\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.discoverhongkong.com%2Feng%2Fplan-your-trip%2